Kendrick Lamar‚Äòs record-breaking Super Bowl Halftime Show was memorable for a variety of reasons, but no moment from his 10-minute show at Caesars Superdome in New Orleans in February took off online and in pop culture quite as much as his delivery of, ‚ÄúSay, Drake ‚Ä¶‚Äù during ‚ÄúNot Like Us,‚Äù staring straight into the camera with a s‚Äìt-eating grin and his now-iconic bootcut jeans flaring at his ankles.

Weeks later, Drake‚Äôs lawyers added the performance to Drizzy‚Äôs defamation lawsuit against Universal Music Group regarding the lyrics on Dot‚Äôs Billboard Hot 100 chart-topper. Lamar, however, would go on after the Super Bowl to win song and record of the year at the Grammys for ‚ÄúNot Like Us.‚Äù

