In April, Katy Perry joined Blue Origin‚Äôs very first all-woman flight crew, launching into space alongside Gayle King, Lauren Sanchez and more for a mission that lasted just 11 minutes or so. Their craft reached approximately 62 miles above Earth to fly through an area called the ‚ÄúK√°rm√°n line,‚Äù aka the imaginary boundary that divides our planet‚Äôs atmosphere and outer space.

The idea of a pop star traveling to the final frontier was wild enough on its own for the internet to go crazy over the mission, but Perry unveiling her Lifetimes Tour setlist in zero gravity and dramatically kissing the ground once she landed also fueled many posts and memes for weeks after the fact.

