When Sabrina Carpenter announced less than a year after dropping Short n‚Äô Sweet that she‚Äôd be releasing another album, Man‚Äôs Best Friend, in August 2025, one element of the project quickly temporarily overshadowed the rest: its cover. The image of the pop star down on all fours with a man grasping her by the hair polarized audiences, sparking dramatic debate as to whether the image was empowering, degrading, or simply not that deep.

‚ÄúI was actually shocked, because I think between me and my friends and my family and the people that I always share my music and my art with first, it just wasn‚Äôt even a conversation,‚Äù she later told CBS Mornings of the backlash. ‚ÄúFor what the album is, [the cover is] perfect for what it represents, and everything about it to me just felt so opposite of, like, the world ending.‚Äù

