One of the most inescapable moments on the internet this year was when two Coldplay concertgoers were caught on video reacting quite suspiciously to a kiss cam showing them looking cozy on the big screens at Gillette Stadium in Boston. After the pair turned away and ducked out of sight once their image flashed in front of the entire crowd, frontman Chris Martin joked, ‚ÄúEither they‚Äôre having an affair or they‚Äôre just very shy.‚Äù

Turns out, the two individuals were Astronomer CEO Andy Byron ‚Äî who has since resigned ‚Äî and his company‚Äôs then-HR executive, Kristin Cabot, both of whom were married to other people at the time. In a New York Times piece published many months after the fact, Cabot explained that she had already been separated from her husband by then, and that nothing physical had gone on between herself and her boss before the concert.

‚ÄúI made a bad decision and had a couple of High Noons and danced and acted inappropriately with my boss,‚Äù she told the publication. ‚ÄúAnd it‚Äôs not nothing. And I took accountability and I gave up my career for that.‚Äù

