Nothing could have prepared the world ‚Äî or the Billboard charts ‚Äî for KPop Demon Hunters, the animated Netflix children‚Äôs film that absolutely took over with its music. In addition to its corresponding album becoming the first movie soundtrack to ever have four songs simultaneously chart in the top 10 of the Billboard Hot 100, ‚ÄúGolden‚Äù ruled atop the ranking for two weeks and spent 18 at No. 1 on the Billboard Global 200.

Plus, ‚ÄúGolden‚Äù earned a historic Grammy nomination for song of the year and closed out 2025 as Billboard staff‚Äôs No. 1 song of the past 12 months, while KPop Demon Hunters remains the most-streamed flick of all time on Netflix.

