The backlash to the announcement of Bad Bunny as 2026 Super Bowl Halftime Show was absolutely bonkers, infuriating people who weren‚Äôt keen on having a predominantly Spanish-speaking musician headline the gig. Even President Donald Trump had something to say about the choice, which he called ‚Äúabsolutely ridiculous,‚Äù and Turning Point USA announced plans to host an alternative halftime show featuring ‚Äúanything in English.‚Äù

Benito, however, has remained unfazed ahead of his showcase on Feb. 8, 2026. ‚ÄúI‚Äôm very happy,‚Äù he said in his opening monologue when hosting Saturday Night Live in October. ‚ÄúEspecially for all the Latinos and Latinas in the whole world and here in the United States. The people who have worked to open doors. More than my accomplishment, it‚Äôs an accomplishment of all of us, demonstrating that our mark and our input in this country cannot be thrown out or erased.‚Äù

